	   <tr><td colspan=2>having alot of wis is fine and dandy but remember that AC is also an important factor that most shamans overlook at the lower levels - and for the most part, AC is not a huge deal.&nbsp;&nbsp;But once you start getting higher and higher levels, you want to look into getting more AC.<br>Slow and debuffing can really piss off some higher end mobs, and if they can't be taunted off or taken aggro off you, you want as much AC as you can get so you can live long enough for a heal or for you to lose aggro.<br>I myself have been selling off wis items to get items with more AC - a loss of 2 or 3 wis for an addition of 20 some AC is acceptable for me.  I hope to get much closer to 1k AC by the time i'm in my 50's<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan  2 22:21:21 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>~ Xeblikaa Vyziksha<br>&lt; Wicked Tongues &gt;<br>48 Shaman<br>Vallon Zek</td></tr>
